compliance_note:
**Applicable Regulation:** IEC 61724-1:2021 and EU AI Act (Regulation 2024/1689) Art. 6 / Annex III.

**Required Actions:** The operator must immediately log the DC fault event with timestamp, inverter model ID, confidence score, and human decision (Art. 6 audit trail requirement); initiate a formal investigation within 24 hours because the 5-day fault duration exceeds the 3-day threshold triggering mandatory review under IEC 61724-1:2021; document Performance Ratio (PR) calculation including temperature-corrected values and measurement uncertainty; and ensure all corrective recommendations remain advisory-only, with documented human approval before any autonomous grid-connected asset control is executed.

**Consequences of Inaction:** Failure to maintain audit trail and human-in-the-loop oversight violates EU AI Act Art. 6 and may trigger Art. 9 risk management obligations, risking market withdrawal and regulatory sanctions;
